    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 uses transcript quantification to compute inclusion values (PSI) of alternative splicing events across multiple samples. Given the calculated PSI values per sample, SUPPA2 considers two distributions: one for the \u0394PSI values between biological replicates and one for the \u0394PSI values between conditions.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes PSI computation across multiple samples and events. PSI values are proportions/percentages (range [0,1]) representing splicing inclusion levels. The paper discusses PSI values as the primary quantitative output used in downstream analyses.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PSI (Percent Spliced In) matrix file with events as rows and samples as columns, values in range [0, 1]",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:53:52.224475+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card focuses narrowly on the PSI calculation step from transcript quantification and event definitions. The paper discusses this as part of a broader differential splicing analysis pipeline, but the PSI computation itself is well-documented in the Methods section.",
        "The card does not mention downstream analyses (differential splicing testing, clustering) that SUPPA2 performs after PSI calculation, which is appropriate for a task focused on the PSI matrix generation step."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 2,
