    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/alternative-splicing-event-parsing/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 uses transcript quantification to compute inclusion values (PSI) of alternative splicing events across multiple samples... SUPPA2 currently implements two density-based clustering methods: DBSCAN and OPTICS... These methods generally involve the analysis of either transcript isoforms, clusters of splice junctions, alternative splicing events, or exonic regions.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes SUPPA2 as computing PSI values from transcript quantification and analyzing alternative splicing events (SE, A5/A3, RI, MX), but does NOT explicitly describe a GTF parsing or event definition file generation step (ioe, ioi, gtf files). The paper focuses on differential splicing analysis using pre-computed PSI values, not on the upstream GTF parsing task. The card describes a preprocessing step that is not detailed in the provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "alternative-splicing-event-parsing",
