      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 exploits the between-replicate variability to test for significance... To illustrate our approach and to evaluate the dynamic range of SUPPA2 we used it to analyze RNA-seq data obtained after the double knockdown of TRA2A and TRA2B splicing regulators compared with controls [17] (Fig. 1a). The differences in PSI value for each event between biological replicates are higher at low expression, in agreement with the expected higher variability at low read count. This biological variability provides information on the uncertainty of the PSI estimates.",
