    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/isoform-structure-annotation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 uses transcript quantification to compute inclusion values (PSI) of alternative splicing events across multiple samples... SUPPA2 currently implements two density-based clustering methods: DBSCAN and OPTICS... Clustering is performed only with events that change significantly in at least one pair of adjacent conditions.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes SUPPA2's core function as computing PSI values from transcript quantification and analyzing differential splicing across conditions. However, the paper does NOT explicitly describe a 'generateEvents' subcommand or the production of 'ioi', 'ioe', 'gtf' artifact files. The paper focuses on differential splicing analysis and clustering, not on the upstream event generation step from GTF. The Methods section mentions that SUPPA2 'uses transcript quantification to compute inclusion values (PSI) of alternative splicing events' but does not detail GTF parsing or event definition generation. This appears to be a task card describing a preprocessing step that is not the focus of this paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "isoform-structure-annotation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct transcript isoform structures and local alternative splicing events from a genome annotation GTF file using SUPPA2's generateEvents subcommand, producing three indexed artifact files (ioi, ioe, gtf) that map transcripts to events and define splicing coordinates for do",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:56:07.172547+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/isoform-structure-annotation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 uses transcript quantification to compute inclusion values (PSI) of alternative splicing events across multiple samples. Given the calculated PSI values per sample, SUPPA2 considers two distributions: one for the \u0394PSI values between biological replicates and one for the \u0394PSI values between conditions.",
      "asbval:note": "SUPPA2 is confirmed present in the paper and is used for alternative splicing analysis. However, the paper's primary focus is on differential splicing analysis (computing \u0394PSI, statistical testing, clustering) rather than on GTF-to-event generation. The paper does not describe or name a 'generateEvents' subcommand. The paper states SUPPA2 'relies on genome annotation to define events' (passage 8) but does not detail the event generation workflow from GTF files. The tool is used for a different primary function (differential splicing) than the card claims (event generation from GTF).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "isoform-structure-annotation",
