      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The description of the uncertainty in terms of transcript abundances, given in transcripts per million (TPM) units, rather than read counts provides several advantages. These include speed, as there is no need to store or go back to read information, as well as interpretability and application range, as transcript abundances are already normalized for transcript length and remain stable at different library sizes.",
