      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 enables cost-effective use of RNA sequencing for the robust and streamlined analysis of differential splicing across multiple biological conditions... SUPPA2 is also able to analyze multiple conditions by computing the pairwise differential splicing between conditions, and can detect groups of events with similar splicing patterns across conditions using density-based clustering",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes SUPPA2's use of PSI values for differential splicing analysis and clustering across multiple conditions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "transcript-quantification-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "calculate PSI values\u2014the relative inclusion level of alternative splicing events\u2014across multiple samples for downstream differential splicing or clustering analysis",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:57:41.069666+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 extends this principle to measure differential splicing between conditions by exploiting the variability between biological replicates to determine the uncertainty in the PSI values... The significance of an observed \u0394PSI value between conditions will depend on where in the distribution of the uncertainty it falls... SUPPA2 estimates the significance considering the distribution between replicates for all events with similar transcript abundance; hence, it provides a lower bound for significant |\u0394PSI| values that vary with the expression of the transcripts describing the event",
      "asbval:note": "Core research question is directly supported by passage 3 and the Methods section (passage 8-9) which describes the empirical cumulative density function approach.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Assess statistical significance of differential splicing events by comparing observed changes (\u0394PSI) against the distribution of within-replicate variation, accounting for transcript expression uncertainty. This method provides calibrated p-values that reflect biological noise ra",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:57:52.858244+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here we present SUPPA2, a new method that addresses these challenges, and enables streamlined analysis across multiple conditions taking into account biological variability.",
      "asbval:note": "SUPPA2 is the primary tool described throughout the paper for differential splicing analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "SUPPA2",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:57:52.858244+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The software described here is available at https://github.com/comprna/SUPPA.",
      "asbval:note": "Repository URL confirmed in paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[0].repo",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "https://github.com/comprna/SUPPA",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:57:52.858244+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 uses transcript quantification to compute inclusion values (PSI) of alternative splicing events across multiple samples. Given the calculated PSI values per sample, SUPPA2 considers two distributions: one for the \u0394PSI values between biological replicates and one for the \u0394PSI values between conditions... Given the observed \u0394PSI and Econd values for an event between conditions, its significance is calculated from the comparison with the \u0394PSI distribution between replicates",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes SUPPA2 computing \u0394PSI and p-values from PSI matrices and expression data, but does not explicitly name a 'diffSplice subcommand'. The paper refers to 'differential splicing analysis' as a general function but does not document specific subcommand names in the provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[0].role",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Computes differential splicing statistics (\u0394PSI and uncertainty-aware p-values) from PSI matrices and expression data via the diffSplice subcommand",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:57:52.858244+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 can work with multiple replicates per condition and with multiple conditions. Additionally, SUPPA2 estimates the uncertainty of \u0394PSI values as a function of the expression of transcripts involved in the event, taking into account all events genome-wide to test the significance of an observed \u0394PSI",
      "asbval:note": "Scope statement is well-supported by the paper's description of SUPPA2's capabilities.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope (inputs requirement: replicates per condition)",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You have PSI matrices for two or more conditions with replicates per condition, and you need to determine which alternative splicing events show significant changes between conditions while accounting for measurement uncertainty that scales with transcript expression levels.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:57:52.858244+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 can work with multiple replicates per condition and with multiple conditions... SUPPA2 estimates the uncertainty of \u0394PSI values as a function of the expression of transcripts involved in the event, taking into account all events genome-wide",
      "asbval:note": "The requirement for replicates is implicit in the method's design, which exploits 'variability between biological replicates' (passage 3). The paper does not explicitly state a minimum of 2 replicates, but the methodology requires replicate structure.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope (when NOT to use: unpaired samples)",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Samples are unpaired or replicate structure is unclear \u2014 the method requires at least 2 replicates per condition to estimate within-condition variance",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:57:52.858244+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SUPPA2 uses transcript quantification to compute inclusion values (PSI) of alternative splicing events across multiple samples. Given the calculated PSI values per sample, SUPPA2 considers two distributions: one for the \u0394PSI values between biological replicates and one for the \u0394PSI values between conditions... where r = 1,..,|Rc| runs over the replicates in each condition",
      "asbval:note": "The method explicitly requires per-sample PSI values and per-replicate expression (TPM) values to compute the within-replicate distribution.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope (when NOT to use: aggregated PSI)",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input PSI values are already aggregated across replicates \u2014 the method requires individual per-sample PSI and expression values",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:57:52.858244+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For the distribution between conditions, the \u0394PSI values are calculated as the difference of the means in the two conditions",
      "asbval:note": "The method is inherently comparative and requires at least two conditions to compute \u0394PSI.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-018-1417-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "uncertainty-aware-significance-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope (when NOT to use: single condition)",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You only have a single biological condition \u2014 differential analysis requires two or more distinct conditions",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:57:52.858244+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
